    [Lloyd's of London, the long time pillar of the insurance industry, is 
facing difficult times.]1 [The company has been hit by huge claims from a 
ten-year string of disasters]2 [and is also losing investors at an
unprecedented rate.]3 [The company is slowly making some changes]4 [but it must
face the challenge]5 [of changing some of its long-standing traditions,
especially the failure]6 [to embrace modern technology.]7  


